Commentary Text: K Paul to Bairstow, out Caught by Rabada!! Fuller, slower and wider, Bairstow reaches out for it and drills it straight down long-off's throat. That's the opening Delhi needed. Because he was stretching for it, Bairstow wasn't as balanced as he would've liked to be. And so, that affected - or rather hindered - the power he was able to generate. Went flat to Rabada who made no mistake. Bairstow c Rabada b K Paul 41(31) [4s-5 6s-1]
